  <summary>5/18/1999--Introduced.
Tough on Drugs Act of 1999 - Directs the Attorney General to establish a panel to study and report to Congress with regard to specified issues related to Federal benefits received by persons convicted of drug offenses, including impediments to and mechanisms for denying such benefits.</summary>
